    <h4 class="title">Stroke prevention article</h4>
    <p class="subtitle">Stroke, commonly known as "burst blood vessel" or "cerebral embolism", is the fifth leading
        cause of life-threatening disease in the United States and the leading cause of physical disability. Stroke
        causes lifelong brain damage and has a profound impact on survivors' physical functions and psychology.
    </p>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <p class="subtitle">What is a stroke? </p>
    <p class="subtitle">
        Strokes are caused by rupture or blockage of blood vessels in the brain. Blood carries oxygen and nutrients to
        the brain. If the blood flow to the brain is suddenly interrupted, brain cells will die within a few minutes.
        Post-stroke neurological dysfunction, such as speech, vision and movement disorders, etc. A severe stroke can
        lead to paralysis and coma, and may even be life-threatening. </p>
